<p>High taxes on tobacco products are a proven way to reduce tobacco use especially among youth. The current federal cigarette tax is $1.01 per pack, and the current average state cigarette tax is $1.46 per pack. Two states &ndash; Connecticut and Vermont &ndash; have increased their cigarette taxes in 2011 so&nbsp;far.</p>
